TITLE: Basic Python Iterator Implementation in PyO3
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to implement a Python iterator in Rust using PyO3. The class implements both __iter__ and __next__ methods to conform to Python's iterator protocol.
SOURCE: https://github.com/PyO3/pyo3/blob/main/guide/src/class/protocols.md#2025-04-16_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
use pyo3::prelude::*;

use std::sync::Mutex;

#[pyclass]
struct MyIterator {
    iter: Mutex<Box<dyn Iterator<Item = PyObject> + Send>>,
}

#[pymethods]
impl MyIterator {
    fn __iter__(slf: PyRef<'_, Self>) -> PyRef<'_, Self> {
        slf
    }
    fn __next__(slf: PyRefMut<'_, Self>) -> Option<PyObject> {
        slf.iter.lock().unwrap().next()
    }
}
```

