TITLE: Handling Python Exceptions in Rust using PyO3
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to handle Python exceptions when calling Python functions from Rust. It shows how to catch and process Python errors using PyO3's error handling mechanisms.
SOURCE: https://github.com/PyO3/pyo3/blob/main/guide/src/function-calls.md#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
use pyo3::prelude::*;
use pyo3::exceptions::PyValueError;

fn main() -> PyResult<()> {
    Python::with_gil(|py| {
        let fun = PyModule::import(py, "builtins")?.getattr("int")?
        match fun.call1(("not a number",)) {
            Ok(_) => println!("This should not happen"),
            Err(e) => {
                assert!(e.is_instance_of::<PyValueError>(py));
                println!("Python exception: {}", e);
            }
        }
        Ok(())
    })
}
```

