TITLE: Implementing Rich Comparison with Special Cases in PyO3
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to implement the __richcmp__ magic method in PyO3 to handle comparison operations. This example shows implementation of equality comparisons while returning NotImplemented for other operations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/PyO3/pyo3/blob/main/guide/src/class/protocols.md#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
use pyo3::class::basic::CompareOp;
use pyo3::types::PyNotImplemented;

# use pyo3::prelude::*;
# use pyo3::BoundObject;
#
# #[pyclass]
# struct Number(i32);
#
#[pymethods]
impl Number {
    fn __richcmp__<'py>(&self, other: &Self, op: CompareOp, py: Python<'py>) -> PyResult<Borrowed<'py, 'py, PyAny>> {
        match op {
            CompareOp::Eq => Ok((self.0 == other.0).into_pyobject(py)?.into_any()),
            CompareOp::Ne => Ok((self.0 != other.0).into_pyobject(py)?.into_any()),
            _ => Ok(PyNotImplemented::get(py).into_any()),
        }
    }
}
```

