TITLE: Using Custom Number Class in Python
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates usage of the custom Number class in Python, including a string hashing algorithm that relies on integer wrapping.
SOURCE: https://github.com/PyO3/pyo3/blob/main/guide/src/class/numeric.md#2025-04-16_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
from my_module import Number

def hash_djb2(s: str):
	'''
	A version of Daniel J. Bernstein's djb2 string hashing algorithm
	Like many hashing algorithms, it relies on integer wrapping.
	'''

	n = Number(0)
	five = Number(5)

	for x in s:
		n = Number(ord(x)) + ((n << five) - n)
	return n

assert hash_djb2('l50_50') == Number(-1152549421)
```

