TITLE: Implementing getattr_opt method in PyAnyMethods trait for PyO3
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet adds the getattr_opt method to the PyAnyMethods trait. It allows for optional attribute retrieval from Python objects in Rust, returning None if the attribute doesn't exist instead of raising an exception.
SOURCE: https://github.com/PyO3/pyo3/blob/main/newsfragments/4978.added.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Rust
CODE:
```
fn getattr_opt<'py>(&'py self, name: &str) -> PyResult<Option<&'py PyAny>> {
    let ptr = ffi!(PyObject_GetAttrString(self.as_ptr(), name.as_ptr() as *const c_char));
    if ptr.is_null() {
        if PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_AttributeError()) != 0 {
            PyErr_Clear();
            Ok(None)
        } else {
            Err(PyErr::fetch(self.py()))
        }
    } else {
        Ok(Some(unsafe { PyAny::from_borrowed_ptr(self.py(), ptr) }))
    }
}
```

