TITLE: Disabling Python's Default Hash in a PyClass
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to make a PyO3 class non-hashable by setting the __hash__ class attribute to None, which prevents the default hash implementation from being used.
SOURCE: https://github.com/PyO3/pyo3/blob/main/guide/src/class/protocols.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
#[pyclass]
struct NotHashable {}

#[pymethods]
impl NotHashable {
    #[classattr]
    const __hash__: Option<PyObject> = None;
}
```

